# Viewer UI Lifecycle

## MarkdownViewerApp (imperative orchestrator)

- **`init()`** once: inject `<style>` tags into the mount container, then **`mountViewerReact(container, options)`**, **`await partsPromise`** (resolves to **`{ root, article }`** only). Then **`createArticleInteractions({ getArticle, showToast, getScrollRoot }).bind()`**, **`applyReaderStyles()`**, **`render()`**.
- **TOC loading gate:** before async markdown render begins, set **`_reactHandle.setTocReady(false)`**; after **`syncTocItems()`**, set **`setTocReady(true)`** so Outline can render skeleton while hydration is pending and only show empty text when TOC is truly ready.
- **`updateSettings()`** updates settings, **`_reactHandle.updateSettings()`**, **`applyReaderStyles()`**, and either **`syncTocItems()`** or full **`render()`** per **`needsFullRender()`**.
- **`bumpChrome()` trigger:** not tied to `render()` anymore. Chrome refresh is triggered when explorer/navigation updates current file URL via `explorerBridge.updateCurrentFileUrl()` in `src/viewer/app.js`.
- **`destroy()`** is **idempotent** (`_destroyed` guard): **`_articleInteractions.destroy()`** → **`_reactHandle.unmount()`** → **`container.innerHTML = ''`**; clears **`_rootEl` / `_articleEl`**. Logs via **`logger.debug('Markdown viewer destroyed.')`**.

## React shell boundary

- **`ViewerShell`** calls **`onShellReady({ root, article })`** when both nodes exist. Imperative code (**`MarkdownViewerApp`**, **`article-interactions.js`**) must **not** retain references to floating action controls, sidebar panels, TOC nav, resize handle, etc. — those are React-owned.
- **`article`**: React renders the empty **`<article class="mdp-markdown-body">`**; **`renderIntoElement(article, html)`** and plugins **`afterRender`** mutate **`innerHTML`** and injected nodes. React must not reconcile that subtree.
- **Toast (chrome)**: **`ToastProvider`** / **`_reactHandle.showToast`**. **Sidebar tab** (Outline vs Files): **`SidebarTabProvider`** / **`SidebarTabContext`** — settings for the shell are **props from `mount.js`**, not a separate settings context. **Plugin** hovers use **`dom-tooltip.js`** on nodes created in **`afterRender`**.
- **Loading UI primitives:** prefer shared **`src/shared/react/Skeleton.jsx`** (`SkeletonLine`, `SkeletonBlock`) and **`src/shared/styles/_skeleton.scss`** for chrome/popup loading placeholders instead of ad-hoc spinners or plain loading text.

## Hooks and teardown

- Listeners and timers on chrome elements live in hooks (**`useSidebarResize`**, **`useScrollSpy`**, **`useExplorer`**, **`Tooltip`**, **`ToastContext`**) and must clean up in **`useEffect`** return functions. **`MarkdownViewerApp.destroy()`** does not call into React beyond **`root.unmount()`**.

## Rendering security

- All markdown HTML goes through **`renderDocument()`** → **`sanitizeHtml()`** → **`renderIntoElement()`** (see **`40-rendering-security.mdc`**).

## Themes and Shiki

- Reader preset changes that affect fenced code still require a **full** **`render()`** (see **`35-reader-theme-and-shiki.mdc`**).

## Stable DOM contract

- Preserve shell class names and hierarchy (**`mdp-root`**, **`mdp-sidebar`**, **`mdp-markdown-body`**) so SCSS and scroll math stay valid.
